fields.Title: WORLD / WAITING BENCH
fields.Description: a bench where you (and Kim) can sit and wait for an X amount of time so the player won't get softlocked-stuck in the game for lacking content until daychange!

fields.Title: Bench: "Time passes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time passes...

fields.Title: Bench: "Every so often you catch a glimpse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Every so often you catch a glimpse of the sun still shining, somewhere behind the clouds of rain...

fields.Title: Bench: "Darkness ahead. You don't even know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Darkness ahead. You don't even know what you are waiting for anymore...

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to come up with something f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to come up with something fresh and exciting, but the endeavour only gives you a slight headache.
fields.Alternate1: Sitting on a bench on the coast... it's like a performance piece. But a performance of what?

fields.Title: Bench: "The cold stone slab of the bench lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cold stone slab of the bench looks rather uncomfortable. There are cigarette stubs all around.

fields.Title: Bench: "It's both dark and cold... ultimate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's both dark and cold... ultimately not the best time for sitting on a stone bench.

fields.Title: Bench: "What events led you to sitting on a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What events led you to sitting on a bench, completely drenched? The coast is bleak, the rain is bleak, your soul is bleak.

fields.Title: Bench: "The sun slowly setting behind the h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun slowly setting behind the horizon only brings to mind the sadness of loss.
fields.Alternate1: Is there a life after death? What could it be? You could go and find out... you've been close enough times already. Wipe the slate clean.
fields.Alternate2: Look at yourself, Kras Mazov. It has to be you... it all fits. Everything about it. The revolutionary heart beats within.
fields.Alternate3: Mm, sweet tar... flowing down your throat, deep into those lungs... the immaculate taste...

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to twiddle your thumbs, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to twiddle your thumbs, but ever since you've become a grandmaster the old passion just isn't there. Instead, you put your hands in your lap and wait...

fields.Title: Bench: "It's getting late... time to head o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's getting late... time to head off. The plaza is not for sleeping bums.

fields.Title: Bench: "The bright sun blazing overhead is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The bright sun blazing overhead is making it difficult to concentrate on deep thoughts.
fields.Alternate1: I am the Law. I am *the Law*. *I am* The Law.
fields.Alternate2: How well would a melody complement Egg Head's aggressive beat? Can he truly craft something extremely new and exciting?
fields.Alternate3: There has to be a way to open that fucking door. Unbelievable. There's no such thing as a door cops can't get into! This sucks.

fields.Title: Bench: "After a while of staring ahead into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: After a while of staring ahead into nothingness, you decide it's better to just move on.
fields.Alternate1: Affecting austerity and deregulating the markets could lift Revachol out from this post-war limbo. It surely cannot fail.
fields.Alternate2: Stronger unionization and nationalization of the assets could lift Revachol out from this post-war limbo. And perhaps we should also eat the rich.
fields.Alternate3: We ought to kick out all the work-stealing foreigners, and women too, for that matter. That could lift Revachol out from this post-war limbo.
fields.Alternate4: Moderation and balance are the keystones on this occasion... a straight median path of non-interference helps the status quo prevail.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "You're so close! Almost there. Ulti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're so close! Almost there. Ultimate dexterity is within reach...

fields.Title: Bench: "It is the dead of night. Now is not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is the dead of night. Now is not the time for sitting, but for sleeping. It is time to find a bed.

fields.Title: Bench: "Is Time flat and linear in nature....."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is Time flat and linear in nature... or is it cyclical? It feels as if you're *so close* to figuring out the answer.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It's because of all the money. Even..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's because of all the money. Even the sky gets an aura of glistening lucre.

fields.Title: You: "Sit and rest."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sit and rest.

fields.Title: You: "Think deep thoughts. [Wait 1 hour.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Think deep thoughts. [Wait 1 hour.]

fields.Title: Bench: "The midday sun showers you with the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The midday sun showers you with the warm rays of the spring. It does not give you many thoughts, but it feels peaceful...
fields.Alternate1: Hard core! Are there limits above *hyper*? How out of this world can you get, man?! Ultra beyond-the-barrier hardest core, motherfuckers!
fields.Alternate2: How would it be possible to make Egg Head's beat even harder core?! There's got to be a new, highly experimental way.
fields.Alternate3: Narcomania is rampant in this town... someone's really going to clean this shit up. That someone -- is You. Believe it, narcomaniacs!

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to think of something subst..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to think of something substantial, but your mind keeps getting caught on all the paperwork you have to do... later... eventually...
fields.Alternate1: What if it's possible to take superstardom to a whole new level? Upgrade the Expression and your swaggering suave...
fields.Alternate2: It is perfectly normal to take a quick break during police work. It will help against possible over-exertion, in case you need to run after a crook or something...
fields.Alternate3: How is it possible to be such an unbelievable fuck-up?! Every single thing ends in failure... you just can't get anything right.
fields.Alternate4: The rending. It draweth ever nearer. Your blood almost boils with the anticipation...

fields.Title: Bench: "But you know you do not have the lu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But you know you do not have the luxury to wait... the clock ticks towards the final hour.

fields.Title: Bench: "Your fingers feel stuck. Your mind,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your fingers feel stuck. Your mind, uninspired. This place... this bench, it just lacks the right... atmosphere...

fields.Title: Bench: "Twiddling is surprisingly difficult..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Twiddling is surprisingly difficult... your thumbs keep getting tangled. After a while, you give up.

fields.Title: Bench: "You ponder upon an endless winter t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You ponder upon an endless winter that covers everything in ice and snow. What a struggle it would be...

fields.Title: Bench: "You churn through thoughts for a wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You churn through thoughts for a while, but nothing comes up...

fields.Title: Bench: "The cold stone slab of the bench do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cold stone slab of the bench does not look welcoming at all at all. Your shoulder aches.

fields.Title: Bench: "You squint your eyes, attempting to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You squint your eyes, attempting to find something of interest... No, there is nothing up there except the sky.

fields.Title: Bench: "The twiddling barely keeps your han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The twiddling barely keeps your hands warm against the frigid wind blowing from the coast... After a while you've had enough.

fields.Title: Bench: "You more hear than see the large dr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You more hear than see the large drops of rain fall upon the slowly darkening mosaic...

fields.Title: Bench: "You can barely look up into the sky..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can barely look up into the sky, the sun is bright and powerful... it blinds...

fields.Title: Bench: "You gaze at the snowflakes falling..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You gaze at the snowflakes falling from the sky, wondering about the intricate patterns their structures take.

fields.Title: Bench: "You sit on the cold stone slab of t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You sit on the cold stone slab of the bench. It feels rough, yet comforting.

fields.Title: Bench: "You've mastered the art of thumb-tw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've mastered the art of thumb-twiddling. If there were such a thing as competitive thumb-twiddling, you'd be the undeniable champion.

fields.Title: Bench: "The snow tells of a winter that has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The snow tells of a winter that has not yet fully passed... was this your final winter?

fields.Title: Bench: "The glacial gusts from the sea do n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The glacial gusts from the sea do not a pleasant rest make... you should probably move before you freeze.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Getting late. We should call it a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Getting late. We should call it a day... no point in lingering here on the plaza."

fields.Title: Bench: "It's getting there, but it's just n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's getting there, but it's just not enough. Maybe you just need a change of venue.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A rather uninviting bench," the li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A rather uninviting bench," the lieutenant notes. "I'm not one for sitting on benches anyway -- before the murder investigation is solved."

fields.Title: Bench: "The sun draws ever closer to the ho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun draws ever closer to the horizon; the sky is a panorama of intense colours...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Getting late. We should call it a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Getting late. We should call it a day... best not sleep outside on the wind-stricken coast."

fields.Title: Bench: "The worn and beaten wooden planks o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The worn and beaten wooden planks of the bench do not look overly comforting.

fields.Title: Bench: "You sit on the wind-worn wooden pla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You sit on the wind-worn wooden planks of the bench. Your feet ache.

fields.Title: Bench: "You wonder what would happen if you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You wonder what would happen if you tried to set foot on the sun... it would likely not be pleasant.
fields.Alternate1: What if you are a member of the radical homo-sexual underground? You never even fully considered this option!
fields.Alternate2: Hmm, the Race Enigma... if only you could answer Measurehead for this provocation.
fields.Alternate3: Ugh, the buzz keeps wearing off... your mind deeply considers the philosophical concept of drinking-more-of-that-sweet-liquor.

fields.Title: Bench: "As you gaze upon the rough stone of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you gaze upon the rough stone of the bench, the plaza around you still covered with the bloodstains from the battle... you wish you could sit and alleviate the pain of your flesh.

fields.Title: Bench: "A flock of seagulls flies overhead,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A flock of seagulls flies overhead, heading towards... who knows where. Soon enough they are out of sight...

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to concentrate on the sky a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to concentrate on the sky above, but this time around, the stone underneath you feels uncomfortable...

fields.Title: Bench: "You're hoping the sky on the coast..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're hoping the sky on the coast looks different, more interesting... but in truth, it doesn't...

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to make out some shapes in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to make out some shapes in the clouds above. Through the rain, one looks a bit like a potato...

fields.Title: Bench: "The sun slowly rises above the wave..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun slowly rises above the waves... each beam of light reflecting off the water into a million directions.

fields.Title: Bench: "Time passes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time passes...

fields.Title: Bench: "The evening shade on the sand makes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The evening shade on the sand makes you think of a place which is all sand... nothing but the sand, as far as the eye can see.
fields.Alternate1: The sand reminds you of the dusty plains. Man, if only you could roam upstream... wild ranges call your name, boiadeiro.
fields.Alternate2: You wonder how your gun is doing... hopefully it's okay. You're really starting to regret the poor way you handled your own sidearm.
fields.Alternate3: Contact Mike truly is an unparalleled champion, a paragon of physical and mental prowess with the most inspirational story imaginable.
fields.Alternate4: You know... the sunset would look even more impressive if you had even more pyrholidon flowing through your veins...

fields.Title: Bench: "The worn and beaten wooden planks o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The worn and beaten wooden planks of the bench do not look comforting. Your shoulder aches.

fields.Title: Bench: "But realize now you do not have tim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But realize now you do not have time to wait... the clock is ticking towards the final hour.

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to twiddle your thumbs, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to twiddle your thumbs, but ever since you've become a grandmaster the old passion just isn't there. Instead, you put your hands in your lap and wait...

fields.Title: Bench: "What is that nigh-unnoticeable dot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What is that nigh-unnoticeable dot in the sky? Huh... odd.

fields.Title: Bench: "Your thumbs have started to hurt fr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your thumbs have started to hurt from the twiddling... after a while, you stop.

fields.Title: Bench: "Slowly and lazily, snow drifts down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Slowly and lazily, snow drifts down through the morning haze...

fields.Title: Bench: "It's getting late... time to head t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's getting late... time to head to sleep. Best not stay outside on the wind-stricken coast.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Why are you sitting around on your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why are you sitting around on your fat ass?! Do some push-ups, for gods' sake!!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh..." The lieutenant looks down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh..." The lieutenant looks down the street. "We can sit on benches after we've solved the murder. Let's go."

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "You can revisit the bench if you ev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can revisit the bench if you ever need to pass the time when Lieutenant Kitsuragi is gone.

fields.Title: Bench: "Could you twiddle your thumbs so ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could you twiddle your thumbs so hard that they come off your hands? You try... but nothing happens. You give up.

fields.Title: Bench: "It's getting so dark you can barely..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's getting so dark you can barely make out the snowflakes drifting down from the sky...

fields.Title: Bench: "You try to come up with a few deep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You try to come up with a few deep thoughts, but the rain beating against your face is extremely distracting.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "It looks like an aerostatic, very h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It looks like an aerostatic, very high above...

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Bench: "The sun does its best to ward off t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun does its best to ward off the chill of the coast... it barely helps. As if the world itself has turned against you...

fields.Title: You: "Twiddle your thumbs. [Wait 15 minut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Twiddle your thumbs. [Wait 15 minutes.]

fields.Title: Bench: "Time passes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time passes...

fields.Title: Bench: "As you gaze upon the wooden planks,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you gaze upon the wooden planks, the sea breeze blowing through your hair, you wish you could sit and alleviate the pain in your body...

fields.Title: Bench: "Your hands are getting more dextero..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your hands are getting more dexterous with every attempt. Still, after a while, you give up.

fields.Title: Bench: "Slowly, snowflakes fall on your mut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Slowly, snowflakes fall on your mutton-chops... you try to catch a few on your tongue. They are cold.
fields.Alternate1: Slowly, snowflakes fall on your cheeks... you try to catch a few with your tongue. They are cold.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "You're so close! Almost there. Ulti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're so close! Almost there. Ultimate dexterity is within reach...

fields.Title: Bench: "What if... Dick Mullen and Man from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if... Dick Mullen and Man from Hjelmdall existed in the same world... in like... a... crossover?
fields.Alternate1: Oh man, if we invited Guillaume le Million here, we could create a wave-crashing beach-party of unimaginable proportions... Speechless!
fields.Alternate2: What could be more exciting than sitting on this bench on this beach? Nothing, you conclude. This is the maximum excitement possible.
fields.Alternate3: This case is unsolvable... you should just give up right now and apologize to the whole town.
fields.Alternate4: Come, darlings of the night sky, bringeth down upon these feckless beasts the cleansing fire! The Gloaming beckons.

fields.Title: Bench: "Time passes...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time passes....

fields.Title: Bench: "You gaze at the shadows deepening a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You gaze at the shadows deepening all around you... it's almost unnerving.

fields.Title: Bench: "What if the sun just one day turned..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if the sun just one day turned off... the world thrown into an eternal darkness. A grim future indeed.
fields.Alternate1: There has to be a way to find the way home... it feels far, but it can't be *that* far. It can't be gone.
fields.Alternate2: Everything hinges upon the roll of the dice... the world teeters, balanced precariously on the edge. And it all seems to be leaning towards failure.
fields.Alternate3: You miss the grind of the jaw... the excessive pumping of blood... the rush, the speed of it all!

fields.Title: Bench: "Couldn't everyone just get along? I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Couldn't everyone just get along? If they really put their minds to it...?
fields.Alternate1: Would it be possible to acquire this whole coast? All this real estate... completely underdeveloped. Imagine all the tourists!
fields.Alternate2: Grains of sand remind you of downtrodden people. Multitudes suffering under the harsh and unforgivable heel of capital...
fields.Alternate3: Sand... just look at it. The same tone, the same consistency... this is where the strength of Revachol lies. Uniformity.
fields.Alternate4: Perhaps a firmer grasp from the Coalition is necessary for maintaining order in Revachol... it's always good to have a moderating force.

fields.Title: Bench: "You finally stop picking your nose...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You finally stop picking your nose...

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Perseverance and success... feels s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Perseverance and success... feels so good. Feels *inspiring*.

fields.Title: You: "Stare into the sky. [Wait 30 minute..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stare into the sky. [Wait 30 minutes.]

fields.Title: You: "[Get up.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Get up.]

fields.Title: Bench: "Your eyes are caught on the towers..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your eyes are caught on the towers of La Delta across the bay... it sure makes a pretty skyline...

fields.Title: Bench: "You wonder if it could rain so much..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You wonder if it could rain so much that it drowns all of Martinaise... then everyone would have to go on about their day in diving suits.

fields.Title: Bench: "The sun slowly rises ever higher......"
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun slowly rises ever higher... the morning light makes the air feel glittery...

fields.Title: Bench: "The sky is overcast, rain pours ont..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sky is overcast, rain pours onto the sand and the reeds...
